page.title: 13SWALLOW CLIFF BAY
page.content: Thousands of years ago near Swallow Cliff Bay, was a volcano and in 1985 if you went there you could see a large piece of rock formed by the lava. On our trip to Swallow Cliff Bay we saw the piece of lava. We climbed up some of the rocks and near the top some of the rocks were made of snails and sea creatures' shells.. They had been there 300,000,000 years and you could tell they were old because some of the rocks were rotting away. Swallow Cliff Bay is a pebble beach and you can find lots of sea animals there like dog-whelk, periwinkle, different species of crabs and many other sea creatures. Sheep from the adjoining fields sometimes climb down to drink from the rock pools.
